node.text:
Here is the place  where we are spending 14 days  of quarantine .
We landed on the 8th of March and leaving on the 22nd .
The appartement is great with an amazing view . 
We get the food delivered straight to our door step (breakfast,lunch and dinner) . 
We also can order anything from outside like food , clothing etc...
It was actually easier for the kids compared to my wife and I . We have a pretty good routine . 
Teaching all morning after breakfast and  the whole afternoon free . From 5pm to 7pm  it’s training time and then bed time .
The @wsl gave us a bike to train on and a few training gears . 
There is 2 more days to go !! I’m pretty excited to go back to the free world and show my kids around . 
See you at Newcastle 👍🏼

Voici une petite vidéo tournée à Moorea sur le bateau @akivailagoonadventures . Nous vous proposons une petite préparation de poisson tout simple sur le BBQ à faire après une session de surf ou foil. 
N’oubliez pas la touche finale , 
Le lait de coco 😉.
Tama’a maitai
@signaturefoils

node.text:
I remember going to surf the first CT at keramas a few years back . I looked inside my board room and I saw an old « new » board that was hanging there for a year already . I decided to give it a go during the free surf one day when I got to Bali . I did not know what to expect . To tell you the truth , I did not reAlly like the shape of it . It’s simply not what I daily ride ! As soon as I stood up on it , I could feel the reaction of the board was insane .It actually could hold my lines in small pockets.The name of the model is called «The gamma ». 
Now that’s all I ride when the surf is fun ! 😁😁😁
Thank you @firewiresurfboards  for giving me the best boards !
@wsl

Yesterday we had the chance to visit the Olympic village . I could not believe what I saw. There are athletes from all over the world that are chasing the same dream.
I wish we could stay longer so we could learn from other athletes.
It’s now time to head back to Cali .
Un grand merci à tout le monde de l’équipe de france 🇫🇷. Thibault, le doc , Fredo , michel 1.0, Patrick,corbi et Stéphane vous êtes les boss.

When I was 22 years old , my dream was to be sponsored by @redbullfrance . Why? Because they take care of the best athletes in the world . I’m thankful to be part of that family for more than 13 years . 
Merci de m’aider à atteindre mes rêves . 🙏🏼🙏🏼🙏🏼🙏🏼🇯🇵🇯🇵🇯🇵🇯🇵🇯🇵

node.text:
What a day . First of all I want to thank the #teamfrance 🇫🇷 for the support and the positive vibe for the past 2 years . It has been a long journey all together and mixed of emotions.I finished at the 5th place this year (better than nothing)
I want to thank all my sponsors for always believing in me .
Thank you @isasurfing  and the @olympics  for putting surfing at the top of the game .
Today I lost against gabby but I’m not sad. I gave my best and I knew who I was surfing against .
Thanks to everyone for sending me positive messages during this event , I deeply appreciate it.
Thanks to my wife @vaimitibourez and kids for always putting a smile on my face . 
Thanks to all the Tahitians and French people for the strong mana . I felt stronger than ever because of you all .
Huge love ❤️ to everyone 
#whenitsonitson #tokyo
